WEBVTT

01:12.338 --> 01:14.607
- I love you, Henry.

01:51.978 --> 01:53.445
- Mr. Dawles?

01:53.446 --> 01:54.646
- I'm Henry Dawles.

01:54.647 --> 01:57.015
- I'm an associate
of Mr. Remiel.

01:57.016 --> 02:00.053
Please, get in.

02:24.777 --> 02:26.578
Mr. Remiel's very appreciative

02:26.579 --> 02:28.814
of you coming on
such short notice.

02:28.815 --> 02:29.749
We do hope it wasn't

02:29.750 --> 02:30.949
too much of an inconvenience.

02:30.950 --> 02:33.685
- Oh, not at all.

02:33.686 --> 02:35.020
To be honest, I needed the work.

02:35.021 --> 02:37.289
It hasn't really
been easy to come by.

02:37.290 --> 02:38.824
- Ah.

02:38.825 --> 02:40.125
Well, then I hope
this is the first step

02:40.126 --> 02:43.128
toward reversing your fortune.

02:43.129 --> 02:44.363
- Yeah, me, too.

02:44.364 --> 02:46.732
My wife and I, we're
expecting a kid.

02:46.733 --> 02:48.934
- Congratulations, Mr. Dawles.

02:48.935 --> 02:50.169
- Thank you.

02:50.170 --> 02:52.137
- Is this your first?

02:52.138 --> 02:55.340
- Yes, it is.

02:55.341 --> 02:56.742
- Might I ask,

02:56.743 --> 02:58.544
boy or girl?

02:58.545 --> 03:00.045
- We actually don't know.

03:00.046 --> 03:01.046
- Ah.

03:01.047 --> 03:02.681
Another surprise.

03:02.682 --> 03:05.518
How delightful.

03:08.621 --> 03:10.489
Don't worry, Mr. Dawles.

03:10.490 --> 03:14.060
This bridge has
proven quite reliable.

03:25.572 --> 03:27.139
- We're sorry, your call

03:27.140 --> 03:28.840
did not go through.

03:28.841 --> 03:30.042
- I wouldn't fidget
with that too much,

03:30.043 --> 03:33.880
Mr. Dawles, service
out here can be scarce.

03:34.681 --> 03:36.248
- Great.

03:36.249 --> 03:37.950
My wife's gonna think
I left for good.

03:37.951 --> 03:39.952
- I'm sure she'll understand.

03:39.953 --> 03:41.620
- I don't think so.

03:41.621 --> 03:43.222
- Ah.

03:43.223 --> 03:45.190
Well,

03:45.191 --> 03:47.760
here we are.

04:26.399 --> 04:28.700
It's a beautiful
structure, isn't it?

04:28.701 --> 04:30.369
- Late 18th century?

04:30.370 --> 04:31.970
- Precisely.

04:31.971 --> 04:33.605
Word to the wise, Mr. Dawles,

04:33.606 --> 04:37.309
Mr. Remiel can be a
rather demanding soul.

04:37.310 --> 04:40.145
Just do ask he asks
and I promise you

04:40.146 --> 04:43.582
the compensation can
be quite generous.

04:43.583 --> 04:44.950
- Let me give you
a little something.

04:44.951 --> 04:47.552
- No need for
gratuity, Mr. Dawles.

04:47.553 --> 04:50.656
It's all been taken care of.

04:50.657 --> 04:51.990
- Thank you.

04:51.991 --> 04:53.892
When can we expect you back?

04:53.893 --> 04:55.160
- Hmm.

04:55.161 --> 04:58.898
Well, that is entirely
up to you, Mr. Dawles.

04:59.866 --> 05:02.267
Oh, uh, yes.

05:02.268 --> 05:04.536
Have a good stay.

05:04.537 --> 05:06.205
Hmm?

05:35.568 --> 05:37.336
- May I help you?

05:37.337 --> 05:39.004
- I'm Henry Dawles.

05:39.005 --> 05:41.206
Here to appraise the estate.

05:41.207 --> 05:43.141
- Mr. Remiel has
put you in the north

05:43.142 --> 05:47.346
end of the house,
overlooking the pond.

05:47.347 --> 05:49.981
Once you've settled,
you're to join him

05:49.982 --> 05:53.186
for a nightcap in the library.

06:05.498 --> 06:08.835
This will be your room.

06:11.170 --> 06:12.371
You'll find the bathroom at

06:12.372 --> 06:14.506
the far end of the hall.

06:14.507 --> 06:17.243
- It's wonderful, thank you.

07:56.843 --> 07:59.177
- It is widely believed

07:59.178 --> 08:03.449
that Bach died from
complications of eye surgery.

08:04.450 --> 08:06.818
An infection festered

08:06.819 --> 08:08.687
when a traveling
oculist attempted

08:08.688 --> 08:11.089
to remove cataracts

08:11.090 --> 08:13.525
from his eyes.

08:13.526 --> 08:16.828
The procedure failed mightily

08:16.829 --> 08:19.898
and within four months,

08:19.899 --> 08:22.868
Bach was dead.

08:22.869 --> 08:25.070
The greatest composer the world

08:25.071 --> 08:27.572
has ever known

08:27.573 --> 08:30.709
chose to fight his blind fate

08:30.710 --> 08:34.614
rather than accept it.

08:35.481 --> 08:39.885
Pride was his undoing.

08:39.885 --> 08:42.419
- I'm not proud, but I am happy

08:42.421 --> 08:43.922
and happiness blinds, I think,

08:43.923 --> 08:46.091
more than pride.

08:46.092 --> 08:47.826
- Alexandre Dumas.

08:47.827 --> 08:49.694
- The Count of Monte Cristo.

08:49.695 --> 08:51.162
My wife made me read it.

08:51.163 --> 08:52.697
- Smart woman.

08:52.698 --> 08:54.366
- You have no idea.

08:54.367 --> 08:56.234
- Mr. Dawles, I presume.

08:56.235 --> 08:58.870
- Please, call me Henry.

08:58.871 --> 09:00.171
- Come, Henry,

09:00.172 --> 09:02.541
join me by the fire.

09:02.542 --> 09:05.810
I hope your journey
wasn't too uncomfortable.

09:05.811 --> 09:07.979
- Oh no, not at all.

09:07.980 --> 09:09.447
- Would you care to join me for

09:09.448 --> 09:11.116
an evening spirit?

09:11.117 --> 09:14.020
- Yes, I would love to.

09:23.796 --> 09:26.332
Thank you.

09:27.500 --> 09:30.736
- Thank you, Mrs. Gates.

09:32.438 --> 09:34.205
Cheers.

09:34.206 --> 09:35.741
- Cheers.

09:43.349 --> 09:46.117
You've got a
beautiful home here.

09:46.118 --> 09:47.586
- Thank you.

09:47.587 --> 09:51.591
Sadly, I'm the last
of a dying breed.

09:52.825 --> 09:55.360
I fear once I'm gone,

09:55.361 --> 09:57.896
the estate will follow suit.

09:57.897 --> 09:59.931
- No family?

09:59.932 --> 10:04.270
- My late wife was
unable to bear children.

10:05.838 --> 10:09.541
Adoption was always
a conversation,

10:09.542 --> 10:12.444
rather than reality.

10:12.445 --> 10:15.513
- I apologize if I'm
overstepping my bounds,

10:15.514 --> 10:17.816
but without a
beneficiary, why bother

10:17.817 --> 10:20.318
with the appraisal?

10:20.319 --> 10:23.121
- Curiosity, I suppose.

10:23.122 --> 10:27.158
Even I don't know
everything about this place.

10:27.159 --> 10:29.694
Then again,

10:29.695 --> 10:32.864
maybe I just wanted the company.

10:32.865 --> 10:34.866
- Well then,

10:34.867 --> 10:37.636
to paid company.

10:37.637 --> 10:40.573
- To you, Henry.

10:44.010 --> 10:48.346
My old body is
begging for some rest.

10:48.347 --> 10:51.816
Feel free to look around
the place, if you like.

10:51.817 --> 10:54.119
I'll see you in the
morning for breakfast.

10:54.120 --> 10:55.787
Goodnight, Henry.

10:55.788 --> 10:58.257
- Goodnight.

14:56.095 --> 14:57.395
- Mr. Dawles.

14:57.396 --> 15:01.099
The attic is very
dangerous at night.

15:01.100 --> 15:04.969
May I suggest you
wait 'til morning?

15:04.970 --> 15:07.171
- Of course.

15:07.172 --> 15:10.943
- Good evening, Mr. Dawles.

16:42.701 --> 16:45.870
- Back there, about 300 yards,

16:45.871 --> 16:47.972
my mother built herself a little

16:47.973 --> 16:50.508
home away from home.

16:50.509 --> 16:54.813
We lovingly refer
to it as a madhouse.

16:55.647 --> 16:58.182
A small cottage where she could

16:58.183 --> 17:00.752
cool the daily agitations

17:00.753 --> 17:03.521
that my father presented her.

17:03.522 --> 17:07.325
You see, my father
was a drinker.

17:07.326 --> 17:09.694
My mother was a Methodist.

17:12.998 --> 17:15.733
- Well, my parents
divorced when I was 15.

17:15.733 --> 17:18.002
Maybe your mother
was on to something.

17:18.002 --> 17:20.137
- Maybe she was.

17:20.138 --> 17:22.574
Maybe she was.

17:25.444 --> 17:29.515
The house has been vacant
for over two decades.

17:30.315 --> 17:32.984
Due to my declining health,

17:32.985 --> 17:36.422
I haven't seen it
nearly that long.

17:41.060 --> 17:42.693
Would you mind
taking a few pictures

17:42.694 --> 17:45.263
to share with me
at dinner tonight?

17:45.264 --> 17:47.565
- Yeah, whatever you need.

17:47.566 --> 17:50.068
- Thank you.

17:50.069 --> 17:54.339
Holler if you need anything.

19:40.145 --> 19:41.513
- No way.

20:53.752 --> 20:54.752
Not bad.

21:15.474 --> 21:17.209
Holy shit!

22:37.155 --> 22:39.824
- I'm sad to say,

22:39.825 --> 22:41.459
he is not the first that we've

22:41.460 --> 22:45.196
dealt with over the years.

22:45.197 --> 22:48.399
Transients, drifters,

22:48.400 --> 22:51.569
even fugitives

22:51.570 --> 22:54.939
have sought asylum in our woods.

22:54.940 --> 22:57.241
Property this large

22:57.242 --> 23:00.979
lends itself to stowaways.

23:02.047 --> 23:04.982
Did you find anything
else on the body?

23:04.983 --> 23:07.752
Any sort of identification?

23:07.753 --> 23:10.121
- No, I didn't look.

23:10.122 --> 23:13.891
Legally, I shouldn't have
even touched the note.

23:13.892 --> 23:16.394
- What a sin.

23:16.395 --> 23:20.297
To give up on life so easily.

23:20.298 --> 23:23.300
- Well, we should
call the police.

23:23.301 --> 23:26.337
- I'll take care of
that, Mr. Dawles.

23:26.338 --> 23:29.206
I'll see that the body
is properly disposed of.

23:29.207 --> 23:31.809
- Disposed of?

23:31.810 --> 23:34.979
- Poor choice of words.

23:34.980 --> 23:38.850
A proper burial, of course.

23:40.252 --> 23:44.155
I do hope you'll stay
and finish the appraisal.

23:44.156 --> 23:47.892
I'm prepared to
offer you greater pay

23:47.893 --> 23:51.328
to compensate for
today's unpleasantries.

23:51.329 --> 23:55.332
- I don't think that
would be appropriate.

23:55.333 --> 23:57.601
- $5,000.

23:57.602 --> 24:00.771
On top of your fee.

24:00.772 --> 24:01.772
- That's a sizable offer.

24:01.773 --> 24:05.210
- $7,000.

24:09.281 --> 24:10.815
- Mr. Remiel, I
think you should find

24:10.816 --> 24:13.418
someone else.

24:15.921 --> 24:18.456
- Tell me, Mr. Dawles,

24:18.457 --> 24:22.793
just what will your
departure accomplish, hmm?

24:22.794 --> 24:26.964
An ethical victory?

24:26.965 --> 24:29.700
Moral triumph?

24:29.701 --> 24:31.101
Because it certainly won't help

24:31.102 --> 24:34.772
to take care of your wife.

24:34.773 --> 24:38.275
Or your unborn child.

24:38.276 --> 24:40.711
- How do you know
about my family?

24:40.712 --> 24:42.847
- My driver and I,

24:42.848 --> 24:45.516
we spoke.

24:45.517 --> 24:47.551
I understand this
job is very important

24:47.552 --> 24:50.287
to you, Mr. Dawles.

24:50.288 --> 24:52.289
- Yeah.

24:52.290 --> 24:54.692
It is.

24:54.693 --> 24:58.329
- I am offering you a
great deal of money.

24:58.330 --> 25:01.799
Enough to spoil
your growing family.

25:01.800 --> 25:04.034
Please,

25:04.035 --> 25:07.671
don't allow a fool's
poor judgement

25:07.672 --> 25:11.376
to determine yours.

25:12.844 --> 25:15.279
- $10,000.

25:15.280 --> 25:18.182
On top of my fee.

25:18.183 --> 25:21.286
- We have a deal.

25:24.923 --> 25:28.527
I do hope you enjoy lamb.

25:30.629 --> 25:31.996
- The madhouse definitely has

25:31.997 --> 25:33.597
some interesting stuff.

25:33.598 --> 25:36.701
Like that, for instance.

25:38.436 --> 25:40.471
- Yes.

25:40.472 --> 25:44.208
We named him Henry,
coincidentally.

25:44.209 --> 25:47.378
He was a gift to my mother.

25:47.379 --> 25:49.613
Brought back from China

25:49.614 --> 25:52.283
nearly 60 years ago.

25:52.284 --> 25:54.285
- Well, that's quite a gift.

25:54.286 --> 25:55.920
- My family has never been one

25:55.921 --> 25:58.522
for the obvious, Mr. Dawles.

25:58.523 --> 26:00.391
Can I take a look?

26:00.392 --> 26:03.394
That is beautiful.

26:03.395 --> 26:05.396
You have quite an eye.

26:05.397 --> 26:07.264
- I've had a lot of practice.

26:07.265 --> 26:08.866
- In what way?

26:08.867 --> 26:10.534
- I used to be a photographer.

26:10.535 --> 26:12.236
- Professionally?

26:12.237 --> 26:14.438
- Yep, for a number of years.

26:14.439 --> 26:15.973
I had my own studio

26:15.974 --> 26:18.509
in this broken down warehouse.

26:18.510 --> 26:20.444
I mean, we had brown water

26:20.445 --> 26:22.846
and the occasional rat, but

26:22.847 --> 26:25.516
I loved everything
about that place.

26:25.517 --> 26:28.419
- What changed?

26:28.420 --> 26:31.089
- It's a long story.

26:34.259 --> 26:37.629
- I have all the
time in the world.

26:41.199 --> 26:43.033
- One day, this
drop-dead brunette

26:43.034 --> 26:45.569
walked in my doors.

26:45.570 --> 26:47.471
She had these little
cut-off shorts,

26:47.472 --> 26:49.173
porcelain skin.

26:49.174 --> 26:50.174
Honestly, she was
the most beautiful

26:50.175 --> 26:52.309
thing I'd ever seen.

26:52.310 --> 26:54.411
She asked me if
I took head-shots.

26:54.412 --> 26:57.214
She wanted to be an
actress out in Hollywood.

26:57.215 --> 26:59.750
Now, I had never taken
a headshot in my life.

26:59.751 --> 27:01.085
But I lied right to her face and

27:01.086 --> 27:05.489
said with a smile,
of course I do.

27:05.490 --> 27:06.957
Tragically enough,
that young lady

27:06.958 --> 27:08.692
never did make it to Hollywood.

27:08.693 --> 27:10.494
- Oh?

27:10.495 --> 27:13.999
- Because I married
her three months later.

27:16.434 --> 27:19.069
About a year after the marriage,

27:19.070 --> 27:21.171
my business was failing.

27:21.172 --> 27:23.774
The market was diluted.

27:23.775 --> 27:25.376
My father-in-law had
thrown me a line,

27:25.377 --> 27:27.211
he offered me this gig.

27:27.212 --> 27:28.946
Steady pay, good benefits

27:28.947 --> 27:30.080
and we wanted to start a family,

27:30.081 --> 27:33.485
so I couldn't afford to say no.

27:35.353 --> 27:37.521
Closed the studio, sold
all of my equipment

27:37.522 --> 27:41.326
and that's that.

27:45.463 --> 27:50.034
- How easily we betray
the things we love.

27:50.035 --> 27:52.202
- Yeah.

27:52.203 --> 27:55.272
- That's enough
reminiscing for one night.

27:55.273 --> 27:59.443
Now try to get some
rest, Mr. Dawles.

27:59.444 --> 28:01.478
I have something
special to show you

28:01.479 --> 28:03.480
in the morning.

28:03.481 --> 28:06.618
- Looking forward to it.

28:08.019 --> 28:09.820
- Have a good night, Henry.

28:09.821 --> 28:11.923
- You, too.

28:51.863 --> 28:53.497
- We're sorry, your call

28:53.498 --> 28:55.734
did not go through.

29:04.442 --> 29:05.909
- We're sorry, your call

29:05.910 --> 29:08.113
did not go through.

30:35.867 --> 30:38.169
- Ahh, shit.

31:33.291 --> 31:36.260
- Good morning.

31:36.261 --> 31:38.028
- Coffee.

31:38.029 --> 31:39.296
- Thanks.

31:39.297 --> 31:42.332
Big tray for a little cup.

31:42.333 --> 31:44.401
- May I get you anything else?

31:44.402 --> 31:47.171
- No, ma'am.

32:05.556 --> 32:09.594
- Something on your mind?

32:10.862 --> 32:13.163
- You got any horses
in that stable?

32:13.164 --> 32:14.765
- Not for many years.

32:14.766 --> 32:17.434
I never took much to them.

32:17.435 --> 32:19.603
And in return,

32:19.604 --> 32:22.506
they never took much to me.

32:22.507 --> 32:24.608
Shall we?

32:24.609 --> 32:29.112
This farm has been in our
family for generations.

32:29.113 --> 32:33.517
Centuries of history
under our very feet.

32:33.518 --> 32:38.589
At one time, the main
house was an inn.

32:39.390 --> 32:40.657
A bed and breakfast of sorts for

32:40.658 --> 32:45.295
travelers heading north
into the mountains.

32:45.296 --> 32:48.465
Many nights, I've
imagined all the souls

32:48.466 --> 32:51.335
that must have
passed through here.

32:51.336 --> 32:55.807
Each with their
own story to tell.

32:57.842 --> 33:00.979
Ah, here we are.

33:34.679 --> 33:37.849
- We've been looking for you.

33:43.955 --> 33:46.456
- Tell me that their beauty

33:46.457 --> 33:49.493
isn't absolutely undeniable.

33:49.494 --> 33:51.595
- These are incredible.

33:51.596 --> 33:53.964
- Each and every piece

33:53.965 --> 33:57.701
machined from scratch.

33:57.702 --> 34:02.105
10,000 hours to create.

34:02.106 --> 34:03.441
- Did you build these?

34:04.275 --> 34:05.942
- Oh, no.

34:05.943 --> 34:08.712
I'm not nearly patient enough.

34:08.713 --> 34:11.681
'Twas my father who made them.

34:11.681 --> 34:12.483
- Amazing.

34:12.484 --> 34:13.516
Do they still run?

34:13.518 --> 34:14.951
- Of course.

34:14.952 --> 34:16.152
Though I wouldn't dare venture

34:16.154 --> 34:19.690
them out on that
old track out there.

34:20.491 --> 34:22.826
I can't help but feel

34:22.827 --> 34:25.295
that the majority of people take

34:25.295 --> 34:28.598
the world's beauty for granted.

34:28.599 --> 34:32.668
It's time spent incepting,

34:32.670 --> 34:37.074
designing, creating

34:37.074 --> 34:40.744
all that is.

34:40.745 --> 34:45.514
These objects in space.

34:45.516 --> 34:48.018
Needless to say, I feel it is my

34:48.018 --> 34:51.321
God-fearing responsibility

34:51.322 --> 34:53.889
to preserve that beauty

34:53.891 --> 34:57.461
and, when need be,

34:57.462 --> 35:00.797
give it a little polish
from time to time.

35:00.798 --> 35:02.299
- These are works
of art, Mr. Remiel,

35:02.300 --> 35:04.768
there's no question about it.

35:04.769 --> 35:05.802
But I'll be honest,
when it comes

35:05.803 --> 35:07.904
to their worth,

35:07.905 --> 35:10.006
I don't even know
where I'd start.

35:10.007 --> 35:12.943
- That's easy, Henry.

35:12.944 --> 35:15.712
They're priceless.

35:15.713 --> 35:17.347
- Yeah.

35:17.348 --> 35:19.116
- Through there,
you'll find a staircase

35:19.117 --> 35:22.452
on your left leading
to the storage garage.

35:22.453 --> 35:24.621
Between that and
the machine shop,

35:24.622 --> 35:29.093
you should find plenty
of work to fill your day.

38:23.334 --> 38:25.436
- Henry.

40:53.451 --> 40:55.986
- Hello?

43:42.519 --> 43:44.355
- Oh, shit!

45:25.189 --> 45:28.058
- What's wrong?

47:23.807 --> 47:26.176
- Run.

47:39.656 --> 47:41.592
Ugh.

47:49.700 --> 47:53.202
- Mr. Dawles.

47:53.203 --> 47:56.572
A word.

47:56.573 --> 47:58.808
- Who the hell was that?

47:58.809 --> 48:00.743
- You need to calm down, Mr.

48:00.744 --> 48:02.945
- Don't you tell
me to calm down!

48:02.946 --> 48:04.580
Do you see that?

48:04.581 --> 48:08.017
I was attacked on your
property, understand?

48:08.018 --> 48:12.256
- Are you threatening me?

48:14.258 --> 48:18.728
- I need to know what's
going on right now.

48:18.729 --> 48:21.130
- You're in shock, Henry.

48:21.131 --> 48:24.166
You have suffered a
sharp blow to your head

48:24.167 --> 48:27.336
and I suspect are
victim to a concussion.

48:27.337 --> 48:29.472
- You didn't answer me.

48:29.473 --> 48:33.142
- Take a moment, Mr. Dawles.

48:33.143 --> 48:35.745
Calm your nerves.

48:35.746 --> 48:38.180
And when you have done so,

48:38.181 --> 48:39.982
meet me in the kitchen

48:39.983 --> 48:44.487
for a civilized conversation.

48:44.488 --> 48:46.756
In the meantime, I
shall fetch Mrs. Gates

48:46.757 --> 48:50.193
to tend to your wound.

49:03.674 --> 49:05.641
You have taken liberties with my

49:05.642 --> 49:08.844
